Date: 3 Aug 2006
From: Sandra Stephens <sstephens@inspection.gc.ca>

CFIA anthrax update SK 3 Aug 2006
---------------------------------
Positive premises, 99; pending, 5
Mortality on positive premises, 481: cattle, 323; horses, 6; swine, 2;
sheep, 16; bison, 125; white tailed deer (WTD) 10; elk, 1; goats, 2.
Carcass disposal: burnt 75 per cent; buried 12 per cent; pending or
inaccessible 12 per cent.
By Rural Municipality, with 5 new RMs affected (Lakeland, Paddockwood,
Invergordon, Shellbrook, Elfros):
Kinistino: 22 premises: cattle 87, horses 4, swine 2, bison 3, sheep 6.
Willow Creek: 18 premises: cattle 43, horses 1, WTD 10, sheep 1.
Spalding: 2 premises: cattle 13.
St Peter: 1 premise: bison 10.
Ponass Lake: 3 premises: cattle 1, bison 20*.
Humboldt: 1 premise: cattle 1.
Pleasantdale: 4* premises: cattle 19*, bison 18*.
Nipawin: 3 premises: cattle 10.
Torch River: 10 premises: cattle 71*, bison 44*, sheep 2.
Flett's Spring: 3 premises: cattle 3, sheep 1.
Chaplin: 1 premise: cattle 3.
St Brieux: 3 premises: cattle 7, elk 1.
Prince Albert: 1 premise: cattle 6*.
Moose Range: 1 premise: cattle 2, sheep 6.
Barrier Valley: 1 premise: goats 2.
Insinger: 3* premise: cattle 8*.
Hoodoo: 1 premise: bison 12*.
Hazell Dell: 2* premise: cattle 3*.
Foam Lake: 4 premises: cattle 28*.
Garden River: 1 premise: cattle 1.
Wolverine: 1 premise: cattle 3.
Usborne: 1 premise: cattle 3.
Ituna Bon Accord: 4* premises: cattle 3*, horses 1.
St Louis: 2* premises: bison 2*.
Buckland: 1 premise: cattle 1.
Lakeview*: 1 premise: bison 10.
Paddockwood*: 2 premises: cattle 2, bison 3.
Shellbrook*: 1 premise: cattle 3.
Elfros*: 1 premise: cattle 1.
--
Sandra Stephens
<sstephens@inspection.gc.ca>
