Date: 3 Aug 2006
From: Sandra Stephens <sstephens@inspection.gc.ca>

CFIA anthrax update MB 3 Aug 2006
---------------------------------
Positive premises 16, none pending.
Total mortality on confirmed premises 106 (MB 109): cattle 81 (MB 82),
horses 2, bison 23 (MB 25). Carcass disposal: burn 9 per cent, bury 91 per
cent, pending/inaccessible 0 per cent.
By Rural Municipality with 2 new municipalities reporting outbreaks (La
Broquerie, Brokenhead):
Franklin: 8 outbreaks: 1st death 12 Jul 2006: 7 positive premises, 3
negative: cattle 40, horses 1, bison 23 (MB 25).
Stuartburn: 4 outbreaks: 13 Jul 2006: 5 positive premises, 4 negative:
cattle 34.
Piney: 1 outbreak: 24 Jul 2006: 1 positive: cattle 4.
De Salaberry: 1 negative premise.
Hanover: 1 outbreak: 31 Jul 2006: 1 positive premise, 1 negative: cattle 2.
La Broquerie: 1 outbreak: 31 Jul 2006: cattle 1 (MB 2).
Brokenhead: 1 outbreak: 27 Jul 06: 1 positive premise: Horse 1.
--
Sandra Stephens
<sstephens@inspection.gc.ca>
